latestPosts.caption:
Tucked away in the heart of Khar, @makanlah.in is a hidden gem dishing out bold, flavor-packed Asian street food with a Singaporean soul.

I sampled a variety of dishes, and each one delivered a memorable punch. 
The Chicken Gyoza were pan-fried to perfection—crispy, juicy, and paired with a zesty dipping sauce. 

The Chicken Siu Mai were tender, subtly seasoned, and elevated with a touch of chili oil. 

Seafood lovers shouldn’t miss the Prawns in Garlic Sauce—sweet, spicy, and packed with umami.

The Mee Goreng was a comforting mix of noodles, veggies, egg, and chicken, hitting that sweet spot between spice and soul food. 

But the star? The Nasi Lemak Combo. Coconut rice, fried chicken, sambal, egg, and peanuts came together in a riot of flavor and texture—pure joy on a plate.

Sure! Here’s a short and casual review you could use:

tried a cup of local kopi boba —rich, bold, and perfectly bittersweet coffee with condensed milk had that classic roasted flavor with a nice kick of caffeine and yummy chewy boba Simple, strong, and satisfying. 

Also tried Iced Matcha Coconut Latte Surprisingly refreshing combo! The earthy matcha blends well with the creamy coconut, giving it a tropical twist. Slightly sweet, super smooth, and very chill. Perfect for a hot day. 

The overall vibe of this place is casual and cozy, channeling Singapore’s hawker charm with warm service and a chilled outdoor seating area. Makhan La is street-style comfort food done right
